criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients aged 18 years or older with T1-3 invasive breast cancer;

          -  Clinically node-positive breast cancer, defined as positive on preoperative axillary
             palpation, ultrasound examination, and computed tomography scan with contrast;

          -  Patients who underwent mastectomy with a positive sentinel lymph node (SLN);

          -  Patients who underwent breast-conserving surgery containing more than two positive
             SLNs.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Neoadjuvant chemotherapy;

          -  Previous history of breast cancer.
